of story, she links explanations for the physical resemblance between parents and children to larger arguments about culture and society and shows how the threads of this compelling conversation reveal the character of a century. A remarkable intellectual history, Breeding not only recasts the fundamental concerns of the Enlightenment but also uncovers the seeds of thought that bloomed into contemporary notions of human perfectibility.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aBiology in literature. 0aBreeding in literature. 0aBreedingzGreat BritainxPhilosophyxHistoryy18th century. 0aEducation and heredityxPhilosophyxHistoryy18th century. 0aEnglish literaturey18 centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish literaturey18th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEugenics in literature. 0aEugenicsxHistoryy18th century. 0aHeredity in literature. 0aLiterature and sciencezGreat BritainxHistoryy18th century. 0aNature and nurturezGreat BritainxPhilosophyxHistoryy18th century. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 18th Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCUP eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066254208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044247208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311045952440uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/davi13878423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231511117.jpg  a978-3-11-044247-2  CUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013  a978-3-11-045952-4  CUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066254-2  CUP eBook Package 2000-2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SS